{"problem_statement": "A particle is acted upon by the forces $3 \\hat{i}-2 \\hat{j}+2 \\hat{k}$ and $2 \\hat{i}+\\hat{j}-\\hat{k}$ is displaced from the point $(1,3,-1)$ to the point $(4,-1, \\lambda)$. If the work done by the forces is 16 units, find the value of $\\lambda$.", "overview": "Calculate resultant force and displacement, then use work-energy theorem to find $\\lambda$.", "step_details": [{"step_index": 1, "explanation": "$\\textbf{Calculate the resultant force}$", "expressions": ["$\\vec{F_1} = 3\\hat{i} - 2\\hat{j} + 2\\hat{k}$", "$\\vec{F_2} = 2\\hat{i} + \\hat{j} - \\hat{k}$", "$\\vec{F} = \\vec{F_1} + \\vec{F_2} = (3\\hat{i} - 2\\hat{j} + 2\\hat{k}) + (2\\hat{i} + \\hat{j} - \\hat{k})$", "$\\vec{F} = 5\\hat{i} - \\hat{j} + \\hat{k}$"]}, {"step_index": 2, "explanation": "$\\textbf{Compute the displacement vector}$", "expressions": ["$\\text{Initial position: } A(1, 3, -1)$", "$\\text{Final position: } B(4, -1, \\lambda)$", "$\\vec{d} = \\vec{B} - \\vec{A} = (4\\hat{i} - \\hat{j} + \\lambda\\hat{k}) - (\\hat{i} + 3\\hat{j} - \\hat{k})$", "$\\vec{d} = 3\\hat{i} - 4\\hat{j} + (\\lambda + 1)\\hat{k}$"]}, {"step_index": 3, "explanation": "$\\textbf{Apply work-energy theorem}$", "expressions": ["$W = \\vec{F} \\cdot \\vec{d}$", "$16 = (5\\hat{i} - \\hat{j} + \\hat{k}) \\cdot (3\\hat{i} - 4\\hat{j} + (\\lambda + 1)\\hat{k})$", "$16 = 5 \\cdot 3 + (-1) \\cdot (-4) + 1 \\cdot (\\lambda + 1)$", "$16 = 15 + 4 + \\lambda + 1$", "$16 = 20 + \\lambda$"]}, {"step_index": 4, "explanation": "$\\textbf{Solve for } \\lambda$", "expressions": ["$16 = 20 + \\lambda$", "$\\lambda = 16 - 20 = -4$"]}], "short_cuts": "Work done = Dot product of resultant force and displacement vector."}